Wait, the code in the first Java program appends the current character only if it's a Latin letter or punctuation. Wait, looking at the code: In the loop over i from 1 to n-1 (Java's 0-based):

char c = s.charAt(i);

if (isLatinLetter(c)) {

   if previous character was not Latin, add a space. append c.

} else if (isPunctuation(c)) {

   append c.

}

So other characters (like numbers, etc.) are not added. So the processed string only includes Latin letters and punctuation, with spaces added before letters following non-letters.
